                        <interp inst="t18200918-310-victim2819" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , and fixed to his dwelling-house
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>SECOND COUNT, stating it to be the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t18200918-310-victim2821" type="victimName">
                     Samuel 
                     Baxter
                  <interp inst="t18200918-310-victim2821" type="surname" value="Baxter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-victim2821" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-victim2821" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , and fixed to a building of his.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-310-person2822">
                  WILLIAM 
                  ATKINSON
               <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2822" type="surname" value="ATKINSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2822" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2822" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a carpenter. I had the care of Mr. 
               <persName id="t18200918-310-person2823">
                  John 
                  Hinton Tritton
               <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2823" type="surname" value="Hinton Tritton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2823" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2823" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's house, No. 46, <placeName id="t18200918-310-crimeloc1780">Mortimer-street, Marylebone</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-310-crimeloc1780" type="placeName" value="Mortimer-street, Marylebone"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-310-crimeloc1780" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-310-off1778 t18200918-310-crimeloc1780"></join>. On the 24th of August, at seven o'clock in the evening, I saw the lead safe. About seven o'clock next morning I found it had been stripped off three dormers and part of the ridge. About three hundred weight had been stolen. Carey worked on the next premises shortly before. Mr. Tritton lived in the house at the time.</p>


               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-310-person2824">
                  JOHN 
                  COOPER
               <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2824" type="surname" value="COOPER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2824" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2824" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman of St. Marylebone. On the 25th of August I was calling one o'clock, and<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182009180107"></xptr>heard a rattle spring - somebody said some men were on the roof of No. 46, stealing lead. I ran down to No. 49, the people opened the door; I went upon the roof, and found Mann there. He said two men had been taking lead, but it was not him, for he came there to sleep.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. HONE. Q. No. 47 is a ruinous house - A. The house next door to the prosecutor's is coming down - the door of it was shut.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-310-person2825">
                  THOMAS 
                  BOX
               <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2825" type="surname" value="BOX"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2825" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2825" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I heard an alarm that thieves were at No. 46; I called two watchmen, and placed them at the back of the premises; the servants said some men were on the roof. I went into No. 45, and found Lemon on his hands and knees behind the door - he said he came there for lead to support his family. I gave him to a watchman while I searched the house, and found Carey in the chimney. I found the lead laying in the same room - it was fresh cut, and some torn off.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-310-person2826">
                  SAMUEL 
                  HILL
               <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2826" type="surname" value="HILL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2826" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-person2826" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. The prisoners were brought to the watch-house. The lead weighed 312 lbs. I compared it with the building, and it fitted exactly.</p>
               <p>THOMAS READ. I am servant to Mr. Tritton. I went on the roof, and missed the lead. It appeared just taken. I found Mann and Cary in the next house.</p>
               <p>LEMON'S Defence. I went there for shelter.</p>
               <p>CAREY'S Defence. It rained, and I went for shelter.</p>
               <p>MANN'S Defence. Being in debt I slept in old houses, and went to this house.</p>
               <p>MANN - <rs id="t18200918-310-verdict1781" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-verdict1781" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 24.</p>
               <p>LEMON - <rs id="t18200918-310-verdict1782" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-verdict1782" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 27.</p>
               <p>CAREY - <rs id="t18200918-310-verdict1783" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200918-310-verdict1783" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 30.</p>
